OL,3,CPub-goers in Swindon being served
OL,4,Cshort measures, inspectors warn
OL,6,FAll pubs and bars were given verbal
OL,7,Fadvice and guidance during the
OL,8,Finspections.
OL,10,FCouncillor Jim Grant, Swindon Borough
OL,11,FCouncil's Cabinet Member for
OL,12,FCommunities and Partnerships, said:
OL,13,F"This is only a snapshot survey but,
OL,14,Finterestingly, the results mirrored
OL,15,Fthose of a national study which also
OL,16,Fshowed that consumers are not getting
OL,17,Fwhat they paid for.
OL,19,F"We want our local hospitality sector
OL,20,Fto thrive, but it should not be at the
OL,21,Fexpense of their customers.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/4
